    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class='post'>
<div style="text-align: left;">Gem Bundling is basically used to maintain all required gems at your application level. It downloads necessary gems and maintain it under "/vender/gems" directory.  Its very easy to use gem bundle.<br /></div>1. Insatll gemcutter gem ( Its gem hosting )<br /><pre class="ruby" name="code">gem install gemcutter<br /></pre>2. Install bundler ( Its<span style="font-family: helvetica, arial, freesans, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;">&nbsp;a tool that manages gem dependencies for your ruby application. )</span><br /><pre class="ruby" name="code">gem install bundler<br /></pre>3. Start using <br /><pre class="ruby" name="code">gem bundle<br /></pre></div>

